The conversation began with Samuel Kwame Dassi expressing interest in a PhD position in Environmental Economics under James Rising at the University of Delaware. He presented his strong academic background, including a first-class degree and a project on COVID-19, highlighting his focus on data-driven solutions for environmental challenges in Ghana. Rising acknowledged Samuel's potential but mentioned funding constraints, encouraging him to apply by year’s end. Following Samuel’s submission of his application, he followed up for feedback, but Rising ultimately regretted to inform him that funding was unavailable for a position. Rising wished him luck in his academic pursuits and encouraged continued communication, concluding the email respectfully.
